Additionally, the paper uses perceptual loss, which is a technique commonly used in image processing and computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also deals with signal processing and information theory, which are covered in the cs.IT sub-category. The use of perceptual loss can also be seen as a machine learning approach, which is covered in the cs.MM and cs.LG sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for compressive sensing, which can be seen as an application of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI a possible sub-category as well.
